	<div class="post" id="post-8">
		<div class="title">
    		<h2>Treatments</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="entry">
			<p><strong>May 23rd, 2008</strong></p>
<p>1st Biopsy</p>
<p><strong>June 5th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>1st RChop to treat Diffused Large B Cell Lymphoma</p>
<p>Result: Grew back 2 weeks later</p>
<p><strong>June 26th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>2nd RChop to treat Diffused Large B Cell Lymphoma</p>
<p>Result: Grew back exactly 1 week later</p>
<p><strong>July 10th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>3rd RChop to treat Diffused Large B Cell Lymphoma</p>
<p>Result: Grew back to almost original size while we scrambled to talk to another doctor at Emory Winship Cancer Institute. Got our first introduction to the possibility of Burkitt&#8217;s Lymphoma. Officially dropped Dr. Amin and collected copies of my records due to her neglect in seeking a Second opinion on my original slides when we asked.</p>
<p><strong>July 25th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>Second Biopsy</p>
<p><strong>August 1st, 2008</strong></p>
<p>Met Dr. Sunnenberg, were blessed to get the BEST Oncologist in Pensacola, and were awaiting FISH Scan results as my Lymphoma almost grew back to its original size. Finally got a treatment before it grew back bigger than before because Dr. Sunnenberg demanded to come to a solution in the meantime with Dr. Flowers from Emory because he was genuinely concerned and very assertive.</p>
<p><strong>August 6th, 2008 - August 11th, 2008 in-patient</strong></p>
<p>1st Hyper CVAD Part &#8220;B&#8221;</p>
<p>Result: Found significant decrease in the size of the Lymphoma. Got results from FISH Scan from Emory FINALLY to discover my correct diagnosis of Burkitt&#8217;s Lymphoma. &#8220;It helps to have other people searching for the right solutions for you.&#8221;</p>
<p><strong>August 27th, 2008 - September 1st, 2008 in-patient</strong></p>
<p>2nd Hyper CVAD Part &#8220;B&#8221;</p>
<p>Result: Significant decrease in size. Almost completely gone.</p>
<p><strong>September 17th, 2008 - September 22nd, 2008 in-patient</strong></p>
<p>3rd Hyper CVAD Part &#8220;A&#8221;</p>
<p>Result: Amazing reduction in size, almost too good to be true&#8230;guess what? It was so similar to my RChop treatments that did not work(even at 3 TIMES the dose) it started to grow back a week later.</p>
<p><strong>October 1st, 2008 - October 5th, 2008 in-patient</strong> (Got in to treatment 1 week early because Dr. Sunnenberg is so assertive and is looking out for my best interests)</p>
<p>Result: It is basically all gone visibly, but we are also considering other options to be realistic about how fast this grows back. Also, he is really concerned for my long term success so we are going to talk to other professionals all over the U.S. to find more cases like mine and make the best over all decision. We are considering <strong>Allo/Auto Stem Cell transplant(a rebirth of sorts) and/or to add more treatments to Part &#8220;B&#8221; of Hyper CVAD(the chemo that actually works)</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>October 15th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>I started my first Radiation treatment. I will do 3 weeks straight twice a day. The radiation Oncologist doesn&#8217;t normally accept Burkitt&#8217;s patients but once again Dr. Sunnenberg has an amazing plan and from speaking with other Oncologists at Emory and MD Anderson they all agree in twice daily moderate doses it will be very effective for my treatment. AND, because it&#8217;s Dr. Sunnenberg I know I am in the right hands for any other specialist I see along the way.</p>
<p><strong>November 5th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>I finished my full 3 weeks of Radiation treatments.</p>
<p>Result: Everything seemed amazing for two weeks or so until last Thursday. Once again there must have been some cells left lingering because I have noticed a significant growth in a matter of four days.</p>
		</div><!-- end .entry -->
	</div><!-- end .post -->

	
	
